		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2616</guid>
		<description>Welcome to a new feature of the site &amp;#8211; Chalkboard Academy. In our house, my wife turned one kitchen wall into a large chalkboard. Not only is it useful for grocery lists and to- do items, but it&amp;#8217;s a great way to communicate as we all run around so busy. I have taken to using [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Welcome to a new feature of the site &#8211; <strong>Chalkboard Academy</strong>.</p>
<p>In our house, my wife turned one kitchen wall into a large chalkboard. Not only is it useful for grocery lists and to- do items, but it&#8217;s a great way to communicate as we all run around so busy.</p>
<p>I have taken to using the power of that communication to send happy thoughts, inspirational thoughts, famous quotes and just generally light-hearted stuff.</p>
<div id="attachment_2618" class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 510px"><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/chalkboard053112.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2618" title="Chalkboard Academy" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/chalkboard053112.jpg" alt="motivational inspirational" width="500" height="373" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A diamond is just a piece of coal that handled stress exceptionally well.</p></div>
<p>I will be posting some of them here from time to time in this, the <strong>Chalkboard Academy</strong>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
