		<item>
		<title>Avengers – a little bashing and a lot of love</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/pH3QEg02nuo/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2012/05/05/avengers-a-little-bashing-and-a-lot-of-love/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 05 May 2012 20:13:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Blogging]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Business & Money]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Culture]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Electronics]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Entertainment]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Movie Reviews & TV]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[captain america]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[chris evans]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[hawkeye]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[hollywood]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iron man]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[nick fury]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[robert downey jr]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[the avengers]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[the incredible hulk]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[thor]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2608</guid>
		<description>Okay, first let me say that I am one of the biggest fans ever of almost every character in The Avengers. I mean, Iron Man and The Incredible Hulk are my all-time favorite superheroes. The thing that I have to gripe about though is the poster. The first thing that jumps out at me is [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Okay, first let me say that I am one of the biggest fans ever of almost every character in <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0848228/" target="_blank">The Avengers</a>. I mean, Iron Man and The Incredible Hulk are my all-time favorite superheroes. The thing that I have to gripe about though is the poster.</p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/avengersposter.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2609" title="Avengers Movie Poster" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/avengersposter.jpg" alt="Avengers Movie Poster" width="500" height="616" /></a></p>
<p>The first thing that jumps out at me is that Iron Man is not there.  <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000375/" target="_blank">Robert Downey Jr</a>. is NOT Iron Man.  Yes, he does an exceptional job playing billionaire playboy, Tony Stark, but he is not Iron Man.  Iron Man is the suit and yes&#8230; the mask.  I get that rich movie stars need their face time.  I get that he needs to take the mask off from time to time to remind the idiot audience that Robert Downey Jr. is such a great actor.  I mean, isn&#8217;t that why ever space movie  character changed to helmets that not only had a huge bubble but lighting &#8220;toward&#8221; the face so WE could see who it was.  And don&#8217;t think I overlooked Captain America &#8211; <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0262635/" target="_blank">Chris Evans</a>&#8216; agent insisted his face was more important than Cap&#8217;s mask.    Don&#8217;t even get me started on Nick Fury&#8230; ugh. Hollywood is so retarded.</p>
<p>Rant aside.  I am really looking forward to seeing this film (and will be in about an hour.)  This has to be the biggest buildup to a fan boy movie ever.  We are talking six feature films leading up to The Avengers as well as cameos in several others.  It is a long time in the making, but I am sure I will dig it.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
