		<description>I posted this to facebook just a few minutes ago: Dawn and I had never tasted an, &amp;#8220;Oh Henry!&amp;#8221; bar so we decided it was high time we did. Meh&amp;#8230; tastes like a cheap version of Snickers. Shortly thereafter, someone commented asking if I had ever tried a Zero bar?  My response was, &amp;#8220;Never &amp;#8211; [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I posted this to facebook just a few minutes ago:</p>
<h6 data-ft="{&quot;type&quot;:1}">Dawn and I had never tasted an, &#8220;Oh Henry!&#8221; bar so we decided it was high time we did. Meh&#8230; tastes like a cheap version of Snickers.</h6>
<p style="text-align: left;">Shortly thereafter, someone commented asking if I had ever tried a Zero bar?  My response was, &#8220;Never &#8211; the white color of the wrapper made me think it has coconut. Not sure if that is true, but not a fan.&#8221;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">It got me thinking however, that there are likely a boatload of candy bars I have not tried.  I think I have a new goal in life.</p>
