		<title>Le Tour is inching closer</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/qdYrtVlqjU8/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2011/05/19/le-tour-is-inching-closer/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 19 May 2011 17:27:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Cycling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Entertainment]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Movie Reviews & TV]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[2011]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[education]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[family]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[france]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[movie review]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[tour de france]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2410</guid>
		<description>Not sure why I am so stoked about this year&amp;#8217;s Tour de France.  I mean, I look forward to it every year &amp;#8211; something is different this time around. It could be that my wife has developed in interest in cycling so maybe I am just looking forward to having something else we can share.  [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Not sure why I am so stoked about this year&#8217;s Tour de France.  I mean, I look forward to it every year &#8211; something is different this time around.</p>
<p>It could be that my wife has developed in interest in cycling so maybe I am just looking forward to having something else we can share.  I mean, we love watching Amazing Race together &#8211; how cool if we could share in this other big part of my life.</p>
<p>So what does this year&#8217;s tour look for:</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">TOUR DE FRANCE 2011</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">Running from Saturday July 2<sup>rd</sup> to Sunday July 24<sup>th</sup> 2011, the 98<sup>th</sup> Tour de France will be made up of 21 stages and will cover a total distance of 3,471 kilometres (before approval).</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">These stages have the following profiles:</p>
<h3>Distinctive aspects of the race</h3>
<ul>
<li>· le Galibier climbed twice,</li>
<li>· 2 rest days,</li>
<li>· 23 level 2, 1 or highest level mountain passes or summit finishes,</li>
<li>· no bonuses will be awarded during the intermediate sprints and stage finishes.</li>
</ul>
<h3>15 new stage towns</h3>
<p>Blaye-les-Mines, Cap Fréhel, Carhaix, Carmaux, Cugnaux, Galibier Serre-Chevalier, Limoux, Modane &#8211; Valfréjus, Mont des Alouettes Les Herbiers, Mûr-de-Bretagne, Olonne-sur-Mer, Passage du Gois La Barre-de-Monts, Pinerolo (Italie), Redon, Saint-Paul-Trois-Châteaux</p>
<p>I can&#8217;t wait &#8211; it is going to be a great year for cycling!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
