		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2400</guid>
		<description>Just wanted to do a quick post to mention that I am now Cinch Casting. Cinch is a great little app by the folks that brought us BlogTalk Radio. You can find my cinches online at http://www.CinchCast.com/chris-doelle . It is to podcasting what twitter is to blogging &amp;#8211; we&amp;#8217;re talking microcasting. Very cool. I am [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.cinchcast.com/"><img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/cinch1.jpg" alt="" title="Cinch " width="200" height="114" class="alignright size-full wp-image-2401" /></a>Just wanted to do a quick post to mention that I am now Cinch Casting.  Cinch is a great little app by the folks that brought us BlogTalk Radio.  You can find my cinches online at <a href="http://www.CinchCast.com/chris-doelle ">http://www.CinchCast.com/chris-doelle </a>.</p>
<p>It is to podcasting what twitter is to blogging &#8211; we&#8217;re talking microcasting.  Very cool.</p>
<p>I am still not sure what it will evolve into.  I am working right now on what I am calling an AppreciationCast or GrattitudeCast.  In it, I will find at least one thing every day to note that I appreciate.  I use the Cinch app on the iPhone and within seconds are recording and uploading. </p>
<p>It is supposed to be auto-updating my facebook page, but that hasn&#8217;t seemed to work so far.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
