		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2388</guid>
		<description>Okay, so I am not 100% on this Paleo Diet yet (see earlier post.) While I have done a good job when my wife is around, I tend to fall back into old patterns quickly without her to keep me honest. The major slip-up has been eating some potatoes (which are no-nos when trying to [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Okay, so I am not 100% on this Paleo Diet yet (<a href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2011/04/19/my-tastebuds-are-changing-my-tastebuds-are-changing/">see earlier post</a>.)  While I have done a good job when my wife is around, I tend to fall back into old patterns quickly without her to keep me honest.</p>
<p>The major slip-up has been eating some potatoes (which are no-nos when trying to eat like my hunter/gatherer ancestors.)  I have also allowed some grains into my diet.  There is just something about the taste of a nice bun or a biscuit that is hard to pass up.</p>
<p>I should be getting my initial blood work back soon so look forward to seeing those results and I promise I will try to do better.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
