		<description>Okay, the reason I am posting this is just because of the subject matter. NOT the water &amp;#8211; in fact, I have often commented that I think Smart Water is the stupidest thing I have ever heard of. I love the way it tackles social media and the need to use &amp;#8220;our&amp;#8221; industry to market. [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Okay, the reason I am posting this is just because of the subject matter.  NOT the water &#8211; in fact, I have often commented that I think Smart Water is the stupidest thing I have ever heard of.  I love the way it tackles social media and the need to use &#8220;our&#8221; industry to market.</p>
<p>Social media is not the latest thing in social media, it is the only thing.  Smart Water is smart in the way they are using it to promote their water &#8211; that is for sure.  Those of us in the business will undoubtedly forward the heck out of the video.</p>
<p><code><iframe title="YouTube video player" width="499" height="311" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Rc47LcvIxyI" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></code></p>
<p>Hate the concept of Smart Water &#8211; LOVE the use of social media! (and Jennifer Aniston is a nice addition to any visual medium)</p>
