		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2307</guid>
		<description>If you&amp;#8217;re like me, you catch a cool Google logo every now and then.  (See earlier post on Jules Verne&amp;#8217;s Bday) I wasn&amp;#8217;t even looking for it but came across a listing of all their cool logos.  I did the thing I never do and hit &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;m Feeling Lucky&amp;#8221; instead of doing a regular search [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you&#8217;re like me, you catch a cool Google logo every now and then.  (<a title="Google - Jules Verne" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2011/02/08/google-honors-jules-verne/" target="_self">See earlier post on Jules Verne&#8217;s Bday</a>)<br />
I wasn&#8217;t even looking for it but came across a listing of all their cool logos.  I did the thing I never do and hit &#8220;I&#8217;m Feeling Lucky&#8221; instead of doing a regular search on Google.  It took me to <a title="Google Doodles 2011" href="http://www.google.com/logos/" target="_blank">Google Doodles</a>.</p>
<p>It has every unique logo they have ever created &#8211; starting way back Aug 30, 1998 when they did a special one for Burning Man.</p>
<p><img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/googleburn.jpg" alt="Google Burning man" /></p>
<p>I have to share a few of my favorites:</p>
<p>May 22, 2006  Sir Arthur Conan Doyle&#8217;s Birthday<br />
<img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/conan_doyle.gif" alt="Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's Bday" /></p>
<p>Sep 29, 2008 Miguel de Cervantes&#8217; Birthday<br />
<img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/cervantes_08.gif" alt="Cervantes Bday" /></p>
<p>Jul 05, 2008 Tour de France<br />
<img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tourdefrance08.gif" alt="Tour de France" /></p>
<p>May 08, 2009 100th Giro d&#8217;Italia<br />
<img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/giroditalia09.gif" alt="100th Giro" /></p>
<p> I still haven&#8217;t gone through them all &#8211; but suffice it to say, there are some really cool ones and a lot of history mixed in.  Fun stuff.  There is even a <a href="http://www.googlestore.com/googlesearch.aspx?category=doodles">Google Doodle Store</a> if you find one that you just have to wear.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
