		<description>Okay, I tweeted that I wasn&amp;#8217;t very impressed with the SuperBowl ads &amp;#8211; okay, I have to confess I didn&amp;#8217;t see all of them. I was really busy with client work and didn&amp;#8217;t even remember to turn it on until the 3rd quarter. Then, I simply started the Tivo and later zipped through the game [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Okay, I tweeted that I wasn&#8217;t very impressed with the SuperBowl ads &#8211; okay, I have to confess I didn&#8217;t see all of them.  I was really busy with client work and didn&#8217;t even remember to turn it on until the 3rd quarter.  Then, I simply started the Tivo and later zipped through the game to watch the commercials. </p>
<p>I found them all posted on Mashable and in between uploads, texting, and various client work &#8211; watched the ones I missed.  What is the result?  There were a few I liked.</p>
<p>Misunderstood &#8211; Chevy Cruze<br />
<code><iframe title="YouTube video player" width="499" height="311" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/qFFWGT_GzYo" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></code></p>
<p>I like old people and it was funny</p>
<p>I also like young people and this was cute:<br />
<code><iframe title="YouTube video player" width="499" height="311" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/R55e-uHQna0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></code></p>
<p>That&#8217;s it though.  Most of them were just lame.  Sure, the Eminem/Detroit one was interesting, but combined with his Sprite or Burst or whatever drink ad he did, I just kept thinking &#8220;sellout.&#8221;  The Tibet Groupon one was downright insulting and offensive too.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
