		<description>How cool is Google today? They honored Jules Verne on the 183rd anniversary of his birthday with a way-cool interactive logo. It is a fun change to the old dependable logo that not only allows you to float around looking out the &amp;#8220;submarine&amp;#8221; logo windows, but turn, go up and down etc. There is even [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How cool is Google today?  They honored Jules Verne on the 183rd anniversary of his birthday with a way-cool interactive logo.</p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href='http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/googleverne.jpg'><img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/googleverne.jpg" alt="" title="Google Jules Verne" width="500" height="201" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2300" /></a></p>
<p>It is a fun change to the old dependable logo that not only allows you to float around looking out the &#8220;submarine&#8221; logo windows, but turn, go up and down etc.  There is even a treasure or two.</p>
<p>Google again stays on the cool kids list.</p>
