		<category><![CDATA[whataya want from me]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2295</guid>
		<description>Sure, hindsight is 20/20 but believe me when I say that the first time I heard Adam Lambert&amp;#8217;s song, &amp;#8220;Whataya Want From Me?&amp;#8221; I thought of P!nk. I mean, it just sounded like something she would sing. I never really thought a lot more about it until I recently listened to P!nk&amp;#8217;s new album Greatest [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href='http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/imagepink.jpg'><img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/imagepink.jpg" alt="" title="P!nk Greatest Hits... So Far!!!!" width="225" height="225" class="alignright size-full wp-image-2296" /></a>Sure, hindsight is 20/20 but believe me when I say that the first time I heard Adam Lambert&#8217;s song, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whataya_Want_from_Me">Whataya Want From Me?</a>&#8221;  I thought of P!nk.  I mean, it just sounded like something she would sing.</p>
<p>I never really thought a lot more about it until I recently listened to P!nk&#8217;s new album Greatest Hits&#8230; So Far!!!  I was floored when I heard P!nk herself belting out the same track.  Now I knew there was some connection.</p>
<p>A little Internet sleuthing later and I discovered that not only did P!nk write the song, but she recorded it before Adam Lambert.  Check out the link above for the Wikipedia article that explains it all.</p>
<p>It was a nice treat to discover.</p>
