		<title>The Tour de 20K continues</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/qBVYyBKjV1U/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2011/01/05/the-tour-de-20k-continues/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 Jan 2011 18:27:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Cycling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Entertainment]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health & Fitness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[History]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[mileage]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[motivation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[tour de 20k]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2285</guid>
		<description>2010 was filled with a lot of new things &amp;#8211; most of them great.  One thing it wasn&amp;#8217;t filled with was cycling.  In fact, it was the second lowest mileage total since I started recording 28 years ago &amp;#8211; yes, it has been awhile. I intend for 2011 to not be my greatest mileage total [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/cycling.htm"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-2286" title="tourde20k562" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/tourde20k562.jpg" alt="" width="278" height="200" /></a>2010 was filled with a lot of new things &#8211; most of them great.  One thing it wasn&#8217;t filled with was cycling.  In fact, it was the second lowest mileage total since I started recording 28 years ago &#8211; yes, it has been awhile.</p>
<p>I intend for 2011 to not be my greatest mileage total ever, but certainly not another one like last year.  In an attempt to get some balance in my life &#8211; I have worked cycling back into the mix.  It seems to be working out.</p>
<p>Sure, it hasn&#8217;t been that long and last year it seemed to be working out as well.  In the end, I know it will be a good year because things are getting better all over.</p>
<p>So, the quest to reach 20,000 cycling miles continues.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
