		<description>Being a nerd, I love using nerd tools to analyze things.  One of the nerd tools I have been using for the past five years is last.fm.  This site tracks (scrobbles) all the songs played on my computer, iPod, iPhone etc. Sure, it doesn&amp;#8217;t get all of them and sometimes it messes up, but it [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2280" title="pink_300x423" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/pink_300x423-283x400.jpg" alt="" hspace="8" width="141" height="200" align="right" />Being a nerd, I love using nerd tools to analyze things.  One of the nerd tools I have been using for the past five years is last.fm.  This site tracks (scrobbles) all the songs played on my computer, iPod, iPhone etc. Sure, it doesn&#8217;t get all of them and sometimes it messes up, but it does a pretty decent job.</p>
<p>Here are the top ten tracks I listened to in 2010 according to last.fm:</p>
