		<title>Leanback or just fall over?</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/SxSzqPEe70M/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/12/11/leanback-not-really-sure-about-it/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 11 Dec 2010 20:05:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Business & Money]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Entertainment]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Internet Coolness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[My Pets]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[http://www.freshmediaworks.com]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Leanback]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[review]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Video]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[youtube]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2275</guid>
		<description>YouTube Leanback is one of those things that just flew right past me. I heard about it today and checked it out. I am still not really sure a) if I like it b) what it is good for c) how I would use it It seems too interactive to be useful from the standpoint [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/leanback" target="_blank">YouTube Leanback</a> is one of those things that just flew right past me.  I heard about it today and checked it out.  I am still not really sure</p>
<ul>
<li> a) if I like it</li>
<li>b) what it is good for</li>
<li>c) how I would use it</li>
</ul>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lean1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2277" title="lean1" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/lean1.png" alt="" width="500" height="278" /></a></p>
<p>It seems too interactive to be useful from the standpoint of watching on your family television.  I mean, I know my attention span can be low at time, but when I kick back in front of the big screen, I plan to not move, not flip channels, not make a lot of choices.  That is something I do before I sit down.</p>
<p>I can see it working from the desktop if you are exclusively planning to sit and watch YouTube content &#8211; but come on &#8211; who does that?  Teenagers?  If I spend any time on YouTube it is while doing other things and I need my screen for that.</p>
<p>Will I try it?  Sure, I will give it a few test runs.  Will it be added to my habits?  Not likely.</p>
<p>You tell me &#8211; do you use it?  How do you use it?  Will it go the way of the Dodo bird and &#8220;Pants on the Ground?&#8221;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
