		<description>The Wimberley Texans (14-0) took off Friday afternoon aboard chartered buses as they headed to the campus of Baylor University to take on Coldspring-Oakhurst (13-1) at Floyd Casey Stadium.  The game will kickoff at 7:30 and the Texans faithful hope it is one step closer to a return to the state championship. The Texans last [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Wimberley Texans (14-0) took off Friday afternoon aboard chartered buses as they headed to the campus of Baylor University to take on Coldspring-Oakhurst (13-1) at Floyd Casey Stadium.  The game will kickoff at 7:30 and the Texans faithful hope it is one step closer to a return to the state championship.</p>
<p><code><object width="500" height="306"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/p33Y1akdHMw?fs=1&#038;hl=en_US&#038;rel=0&#038;hd=1&#038;color1=0xe1600f&#038;color2=0xfebd01"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/p33Y1akdHMw?fs=1&#038;hl=en_US&#038;rel=0&#038;hd=1&#038;color1=0xe1600f&#038;color2=0xfebd01" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="500" height="306"></embed></object></code></p>
<p>The Texans last won a state championship in 2005 behind the vaulted &#8220;Code Red Defense.  Wimberley&#8217;s own, <a href="http://www.lonestargridiron.com">Lone Star Gridiron</a> &#8211; the top website covering high school football statewide &#8211; has the Texans as a favorite in this game</p>
<p><a title="Newspaper, events Wimberley, Texas" href="http://www.thisweekinwimberley.com" target="_blank">Source: This Week in Wimberley</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
