		<item>
		<title>A Pair of Freemans</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/sWHNuX7fOf8/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/12/06/a-pair-of-freemans/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Dec 2010 05:19:26 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Entertainment]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Movie Reviews & TV]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2269</guid>
		<description>As coincidences go, I found this one rather cool. I got two movies in from Netflix recently and decided to watch them both today. When the second one started, I realized they both had Morgan Freeman in the cast. They were, in the order I watched, The Big Bounce and Invictus. There couldn&amp;#8217;t be two [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img style="float: left; padding: 5px 5px 5px 5px;" src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/2_movie_tix.jpg" alt="" hspace="8" align="left" />As coincidences go, I found this one rather cool.  I got two movies in from Netflix recently and decided to watch them both today.  When the second one started, I realized they both had Morgan Freeman in the cast.  They were, in the order I watched, <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0315824/" target="_blank">The Big Bounce</a> and Invictus.  There couldn&#8217;t be two less alike movies, and I am glad I saw them in that order.</p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/bigbouncelso.png"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2271" title="bigbouncelso" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/bigbouncelso.png" alt="" width="100" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0315824/" target="_blank">The Big Bounce</a> was cute, but weak.  <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0005562/" target="_self">Owen Wilson</a> played a small-time crook and it featured a pretty big list of A-list actors &#8211; <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000151/" target="_self">Morgan Freeman</a>, <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000221/" target="_self">Charlie Sheen</a>, <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000641/" target="_self">Gary Sinise</a> and was filmed in Hawaii.  You can see the appeal of signing on for a lame film &#8211; talk about a paid vacation.</p>
<p>Rent it if you are the one true Owen Wilson fan &#8211; rent it if you want something to play in the background while you do your taxes &#8211; rent it if you have no taste.  If not, skip it.</p>
<p>Okay, it may not be that bad, but it isn&#8217;t very darn good.</p>
<p><strong>RATING 5 out of 10</strong><br />
<img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /></p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/invictuslog.png"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-2270" title="invictuslog" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/invictuslog.png" alt="" width="150" height="199" /></a>The next one was a much better film &#8211; <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1057500/" target="_self">Invictus</a> starring <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000151/" target="_self">Mr. Freeman</a> and <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000354/" target="_self">Matt Damon</a>.  Invictus chronicles the parallel stories of Nelson Mandela&#8217;s first months as President of South Africa and the Springboks, their national rugby team.  <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000142/" target="_self">Clint Eastwood</a> does a masterful job of directing.  He is able to set the scene of a country struggling to unite after years of Apartheid rule and still show the humanity of the individuals involved.</p>
<p>Being an American, I really knew little about this time in the history of South Africa.  As a film goes, it does more than just educate however, it evokes emotion around every turn.  Oh yeah, and there is a very good sports story intertwined throughout.  One of Clint&#8217;s great jobs as director and one of Morgans great jobs as actor.  Very good  stuff.</p>
<p><strong>RATING 8 out of 10</strong><br />
<img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /></p>
]]></content:encoded>
