		<title>On being a good person</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/4-Cgpynu6KM/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/10/09/on-being-a-good-person/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 09 Oct 2010 19:26:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Culture]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Friends & Family]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health & Fitness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Religion]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[bad]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[clint eastwood]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[decent]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[good]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[happy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[honest]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[motivation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[self-help]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[ugly]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2241</guid>
		<description>I was asked the other day, &amp;#8220;How do you think it happens that some people choose to be good and others choose to be bad?&amp;#8221; It really caused me to do some deep thinking (weird huh, me analyzing things &amp;#8211; haha). In the end, I said, &amp;#8220;I don&amp;#8217;t think people make a conscious decision to [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/goodbadugly.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-2242" title="The Good, The Bad and the Ugly" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/goodbadugly.jpg" alt="" width="180" height="250" /></a>I was asked the other day, &#8220;How do you think it happens that some people choose to be good and others choose to be bad?&#8221;  It really caused me to do some deep thinking (weird huh, me analyzing things &#8211; haha).  In the end, I said, &#8220;I don&#8217;t think people make a conscious decision to be good or bad.  I think they are faced with hundreds of decisions and just do what their self image tells them.&#8221;</p>
<p>My thinking is that most off of us think we are &#8220;the good guys.&#8221;  Even Charles Manson likely thought that his actions were the right thing to do &#8211; or at least were justified.  I tend to believe that we make decisions each and every day to do &#8220;good&#8221; or &#8220;bad.&#8221;  Sometimes we take the shopping cart all the way back to the return area &#8211; other times we just push it far enough away so we can drive past.  It isn&#8217;t the action of leaving the cart out that suddenly labels us as a bad person, but perhaps it is a pebble in the hill of bad deeds.  The same person who leaves that shopping cart blocking a parking spot may regularly save kittens from trees, volunteer at the homeless shelter, and generally be a decent person.</p>
<p>So what do we do?  All I can tell you is what I do &#8211; try to do good as often as I think of it.  When I am given an option of doing the right thing or maybe taking the easy way out &#8211; I try to do right.  Sure, I don&#8217;t always succeed.  Sure, I sometimes come up short.  In the end though, I think my pile of good pebbles is a far cry larger than my pile of bad pebbles &#8211; and that&#8217;s a good start.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
