		<item>
		<title>My Bogey-less history comes to an end</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/WJbRqfwM6ts/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/09/17/my-bogey-less-history-comes-to-an-end/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 17 Sep 2010 17:24:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Movie Reviews & TV]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[bogey]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[film review]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[humphrey bogart]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[lauren bacall]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[movie]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[rating]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[the big sleep]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2235</guid>
		<description>I know it is hard to believe but, I have never seen a Humphrey Bogart movie all the way through. Yeah, me &amp;#8211; the guy who has rated and/or reviewed over 3,000 movies &amp;#8211; the same guy that LOVES old black and whites&amp;#8230; never has seen a Bogey film all the way through. Sure, I [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img style="float: left; padding: 5px 5px 5px 5px;" src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/2_movie_tix.jpg" alt="" hspace="8" align="left" />I know it is hard to believe but, I have never seen a <a href="http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000007/" target="_blank">Humphrey Bogart</a> movie all the way through.  Yeah, me &#8211; the guy who has rated and/or reviewed over 3,000 movies &#8211; the same guy that LOVES old black and whites&#8230;  never has seen a Bogey film all the way through.  Sure, I have caught bits and pieces of all the greats, just never finished one.  That drought ended recently.  Working on the laptop after the kids are put to bed, I can put on a movie and over the course of a few nights finish it.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0038355/" target="_blank">The Big Sleep</a> (1946) is one of only two Bogey/Bacall pairings and it was a lot of fun.  Bogey is smooth as silk as private detective, Philip Marlowe and Bacall is cool as a cucumber as Vivian Rutledge.  As film noir goes, The Big Sleep is one of those films that defines the genre.  It is easy to see why Bogart became such a hit &#8211; he was a man&#8217;s man and a ladie&#8217;s man at the same time.  It is also easy to see why so many private detective characters since seem nothing more than homage or outright thievery.</p>
<p>The script is smart, the direction is intentional and together it makes for good storytelling.  Good stuff.</p>
<p><strong>RATING 7 out of 10</strong><br />
<img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /><img src="http://www.chrisdoelle.com/goldstar.gif" alt="new media titan, chris doelle," /></p>
]]></content:encoded>
