		<title>Careful what you wish for…</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/SHpMvabkFcg/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/09/08/careful-what-you-wish-for/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 Sep 2010 22:36:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Weather]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/09/08/careful-what-you-wish-for/</guid>
		<description>Okay, I have been hoping for rain the past few days because the cracks in my yard as large enough to lose a small child.  The rains of the past few days have been a welcome relief to the yard and most of Central Texas, but there is a one major casualty &amp;#8211; FOOTBALL PRACTICE!! [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Okay, I have been hoping for rain the past few days because the cracks in my yard as large enough to lose a small child.  The rains of the past few days have been a welcome relief to the yard and most of Central Texas, but there is a one major casualty &#8211; FOOTBALL PRACTICE!!</p>
<p>Three straight days now the boys football practice has been canceled and it is really starting to bug me.  How I long for a couple of hours in the sweltering heat &#8211; for the crack of helmets &#8211; for the cheers when one of their teammates does a nice move or good tackle.  I am jonesing for the sight of my boys busting their butts and improving not only their physical prowess, but their attitude, determination and just plain ol&#8217; grit.</p>
<p>I know I will regret it, but I have to say&#8230;. &#8220;rain, rain go away &#8211; come again another day.&#8221;</p>
