		<title>Part if growing up is owning your immaturity</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/UzgpRn_JLhM/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/09/02/part-if-growing-up-is-owning-your-immaturity/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 03 Sep 2010 00:21:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Culture]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health & Fitness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[be nice]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[maturity]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[mean people suck]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2229</guid>
		<description>I find it disheartening when I run into people who continually blame everyone around them for their situation in life.  I mean, come on &amp;#8211; you are where you are because of choices you have made. I am sure you have all run into those people &amp;#8211; you know the ones. &amp;#8220;I would be a [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I find it disheartening when I run into people who continually blame everyone around them for their situation in life.  I mean, come on &#8211; you are where you are because of choices you have made.</p>
<p>I am sure you have all run into those people &#8211; you know the ones. &#8220;I would be a nice person if ________ just understood me.&#8221;  &#8220;I would act properly if ________ would treat me right.&#8221;  Blah, blah, blah.  Get a clue &#8211; your mistreatment (real or imagined) is not a sentence or excuse to be a jerk, be mean, or be a blamer.  If you do something wrong &#8211; own it, fix it, move forward.</p>
<p>Maturity is not only knowing the right thing to do, but doing it even when know one is looking and even though you would rather blame others.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
