			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Logan&#8217;s team, the HCRA Wimberley Texans varsity team took on the Dripping Springs Tigers this morning in a scrimmage and they looked great.  Sure, there were a few miscues but overall I am very impressed with his team.  The defense played stellar, allowing only one play for over 10 yards and shutting down the Tigers whether they tried running or passing.</p>
<p>Logan played cornerback and did a fine job.  He certainly didn&#8217;t look like a kid who had never played organized football before.</p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/logantackle.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2224" title="Logan makes the tackle" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/logantackle.jpg" alt="Logan and Colby take down the runner" width="500" height="569" /></a></p>
<p>I couldn&#8217;t be prouder and can&#8217;t wait for the next one!</p>
