			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Today was a fun break from the routine as I got to spend the morning at Texan Stadium where the students at Jacob&#8217;s Well Elementary competed in their annual Field Day.  Logan and Dallin got three first place finishes and three seconds between them.</p>
<p><a class="highslide" onclick="return vz.expand(this)" href='http://www.flickr.com/photos/shutterdog/sets/72157624054917826/'><img src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/fielddaywinners2010.png" alt="Jacob\&#039;s Well Field Day" title="fielddaywinners2010" width="500" height="1165" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2185" /></a><br />
If you click on the photo, it will take you to the Flickr set I created.</p>
<p>Overall, it was a lot of fun and I am real proud of the boys for not only doing great, but doing so with class and style.</p>
