		<title>Lead – don’t be a leader</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/UhEKrvD0pnc/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/05/05/lead-dont-be-a-leader/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 May 2010 21:56:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Business & Money]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Social Media]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[inspiration]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[leader]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[leadership]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[management]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[marketing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[motivation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[new media]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[simon sinek]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[social media]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[social networking]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[TED]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[TEDtalks]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/?p=2180</guid>
		<description>I heard this in a TEDtalk by Simon Sinek and it is something I have always believed in. Sinek did a great job of stating it simply &amp;#8211; there are leaders and those who lead. It sounds like two ways of saying the same thing and the verbiage may be similar, but the meaning is [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I heard this in a TEDtalk by <a href="http://www.startwithwhy.com/">Simon Sinek</a> and it is something I have always believed in.  Sinek did a great job of stating it simply &#8211; there are <strong>leaders</strong> and <strong>those who lead</strong>.  It sounds like two ways of saying the same thing and the verbiage may be similar, but the meaning is vastly different.  <strong>Leaders</strong> are those who hold positions of authority, <strong>those who lead</strong> inspire and motivate us.  We follow <strong>those who lead</strong> not because we are forced to, but because we want to.</p>
<p>Do not strive to be a leader &#8211; strive to lead. </p>
]]></content:encoded>
