		<title>Trying out new ap</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RidingWithTheWindowDown/~3/QWM-yuJ0-wQ/</link>
		<comments>http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/03/09/trying-out-new-ap/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Mar 2010 03:07:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cdoelle@gmail.com (Chris Doelle)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Internet Coolness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[ap]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[blackberry]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[wordpress]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/2010/03/09/trying-out-new-ap/</guid>
		<description>I am trying out WordPress for Blackberry to see how easy it is to do a blog post while mobile. Slow typing but so far not too bad. I wish I had a dropdown box for my categories because I don&amp;#8217;t have them all memorized. Now, I will attempt to insert a photo. Not sure [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am trying out WordPress for Blackberry to see how easy it is to do a blog post while mobile.  Slow typing but so far not too bad. I wish I had a dropdown box for my categories because I don&#8217;t have them all memorized.  </p>
<p>Now, I will attempt to insert a photo. </p>
<p>Not sure where it will go in the post but I am going to try a video too.  </p>
<p>We&#8217;ll see <img src='http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>PS. Just found the category dropdown!</p>
<p>PSS. The video was too large <img src='http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif' alt=':(' class='wp-smiley' />
<div class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 2058px"<a href="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/img00277-20100308-17181.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" src="http://www.ridingwiththewindowdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/img00277-20100308-17181.jpg" alt="test photo caption" title="test photo title" width="500" height="375" /></a>
<p class="wp-caption-text">test photo caption</p>
</div>
<p>Okay, so this application is nearly useless for posting images or video.  The only resize option is to 640&#215;480 &#8211; which doesn&#8217;t fit the them and the only placement option is top or bottom of the post.  I guess if I just really need to say something (text only) and it can&#8217;t wait until I get to a computer, this might be a good way to do it.  </p>
]]></content:encoded>
